ZH: 鲨鱼是海洋中的顶级捕食者。
EN: Sharks are apex predators in the ocean.

ZH: 鲨鱼拥有锋利的牙齿和强壮的身体。
EN: Sharks have sharp teeth and strong bodies.

ZH: 鲨鱼的皮肤很粗糙。
EN: Sharks have rough skin.

ZH: 鲨鱼可以长到很大。
EN: Sharks can grow very large.

ZH: 鲨鱼有很好的嗅觉。
EN: Sharks have a keen sense of smell.

ZH: 鲨鱼通常以捕猎为生。
EN: Sharks typically feed by hunting.

ZH: 鲨鱼可以在深海里游泳。
EN: Sharks can swim in deep waters.

ZH: 鲨鱼的鳍有助于它们在水中游动。
EN: The fins of sharks help them move through the water.

ZH: 鲨鱼是非常古老的生物。
EN: Sharks are very ancient creatures.

ZH: 鲨鱼有各种各样的品种。
EN: There are many different species of sharks.

ZH: 鲨鱼在许多文化里被视为吉祥物。
EN: Sharks are considered as totems in many cultures.

ZH: 鲨鱼的学名是“Selachimorpha”。
EN: The scientific name for sharks is "Selachimorpha".

ZH: 鲨鱼通常以其他鱼类为食。
EN: Sharks typically feed on other fish.

ZH: 鲨鱼不会攻击人类除非受到威胁。
EN: Sharks do not attack humans unless provoked.

ZH: 鲨鱼的游弋方式充满力量和优雅。
EN: The way sharks glide through the water is powerful and graceful.

ZH: 鲨鱼产卵后很少照顾幼崽。
EN: Sharks provide little parental care after laying eggs.

ZH: 鲨鱼在许多海洋生态系统中扮演着重要角色。
EN: Sharks play a significant role in many marine ecosystems.

ZH: 鲨鱼的数量正受到人类活动的影响。
EN: Shark populations are being affected by human activities.

ZH: 鲨鱼的口中有数排锋利的牙齿。
EN: Sharks have rows of sharp teeth in their mouths.
